race.description: The Women In Racing Luncheon 24Th Oct Hcp
race.comment: NO CASH HERE (2) saluted two runs ago and not disgraced last time out when in the firing line on the when nudged out in a 58. Finds a suitable race and can bounce back. GAME COVE (9) doesn't win out of turn but ran a strong race last time when beaten half a length over 1200m. Likely to push forward and is one of the main contenders. ONLY THE BEST (5) did well to place over 1000m after he got a long way back in the run. The extra journey should play into his hands, and he's always a chance if things go his way. DELUSIONALDICTATOR (1) hasn't been able to break through for a while, but was tracking well before disappointing last time. INCIVILITY (3) raced forward and deserved the 58 win. Carries more weight but can't be ruled out.
